I'll calculate these financial ratios step by step based on the provided financial statements.

## 1. Current Ratio
Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
= $22,474,420.77 / $3,143,833.89
= 7.15

## 2. Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
= ($6,476,677.56 / $22,876,677.56) × 100%
= 28.31%

## 3. Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
= $3,143,833.89 / $33,082,821.36
= 0.10

## 4. Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
= ($1,938,987.47 / $22,876,677.56) × 100%
= 8.48%

## 5. Cash to Current Debt Ratio
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits) / Total Current Liabilities
= ($627,601.28 + (-$129,032.26)) / $3,143,833.89
= $498,569.02 / $3,143,833.89
= 0.16

## 6. Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Capital Expenditures
= -$16,772,398.72 - $2,729,032.26
= -$19,501,430.98

## 7. Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%
= ($1,938,987.47 / $33,082,821.36) × 100%
= 5.86%
